HEADWORD: vitamin p
<hw>vitamin p</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a water-soluble vitamin that
maintains the resistance of cell and capillary walls to
permeation.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bioflavinoid, citrin.</syn>)⟦br⟧
